    <text>
        <body>
            <head>93. Memorandum From <persName corresp="rectu0ilGsuuTnBLm">Gary Sick</persName> of
                the <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName> Staff
                to the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName
                    corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">Brzezinski</persName>)<note n="1" place="foot"
                    type="source" xml:id="d93fn1">Source: Carter Library, National Security Affairs,
                    Brzezinski Material, Country File, Box 48, <placeName
                        corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>: 1/77–1/81. Confidential. Sent
                    for action. <persName corresp="recHKbRV17rB9OSQC">Aaron</persName> initialed the
                    memorandum, drew an arrow pointing to <persName corresp="rectu0ilGsuuTnBLm"
                        >Sick</persName>’s name, and wrote: “Return with it!”</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1978-04-21"
                        >April 21, 1978</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Tank Transporters to <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>
                </item>
            </list>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recHKbRV17rB9OSQC">David</persName>’s earlier call to <orgName
                    corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> was successful in preventing a total
                collapse of their position opposing the sale of heavy trucks to <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> for use as tank transporters.
                However, it was not successful—at least thus far—in getting <orgName
                    corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> officially back to its previous
                position of lobbying with <orgName corresp="rec9JONpI4d5UqDCd">Commerce</orgName> to
                get the trucks placed on a validated list rather than the general license it is now
                on. A validated listing permits us to exercise policy control over sales. A general
                license is only for notification purposes. (C)</p>
            <p>The issue will go to Under Secretary <persName corresp="recs37LoYbHRIvRqV"
                    >Harmon</persName> at <orgName corresp="rec9JONpI4d5UqDCd">Commerce</orgName>
                within 24 hours. Once he has made a decision, it will be extremely difficult to
                reverse it. As far as I can tell, <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl"
                    >State</orgName> does not plan to weigh in on this, although they are still
                trying to develop a collective position. I believe it is essential that <orgName
                    corresp="rec9JONpI4d5UqDCd">Commerce</orgName> be aware of the <rs
                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recrfy3UsY8QMsqLL">foreign policy</rs>
                implications of this case and that they be informed in advance of our concern. I
                have previously talked to <persName corresp="recgU8anwZT3QEtx2">Stan
                    Marcuss</persName>, the Deputy Assistant Secretary, and I intend to make these
                points with him again today. But <persName corresp="recs37LoYbHRIvRqV"
                    >Harmon</persName> will make the final decision. (C)</p>
            <p>
                <hi rendition="simple_italic">RECOMMENDATION:</hi> That you or <persName
                    corresp="recHKbRV17rB9OSQC">David</persName> call Dr. <persName
                    corresp="recs37LoYbHRIvRqV">Sidney Harmon</persName>, Under Secretary of
                    <orgName corresp="rec9JONpI4d5UqDCd">Commerce</orgName>, and make the talking
                points at Tab A.<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d93fn2">Tab A, an undated paper
                    entitled “Talking Points on Heavy Trucks to <placeName
                        corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>,” is attached but not printed.
                        <persName corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">Brzezinski</persName> drew an arrow to
                    the Approve option and wrote: “DA to call.”</note>
            </p>
        </body>
